Nitpick. Don't assign null to the variable when it isn't needed to be assigned. I.e. change the code to:
Long id;
if (type.getConsistencyModifier() != ConsistencyModifier.FORK) {
  id = longId();
} else {
  id = null;
}

I'm also OK with ternary operator if if{}else{} isn't suitable. I.e.:
Long id = (type.getConsistencyModifier() != ConsistencyModifier.FORK) ? longId() : null;

